141static HashMap<Element*, Vector<RefPtr<Attr>>>& attrNodeListMap()
142{
143 static NeverDestroyed<HashMap<Element*, Vector<RefPtr<Attr>>>> map;
144 return map;
145}
146
147static Vector<RefPtr<Attr>>* attrNodeListForElement(Element& element)
148{
149 if (!element.hasSyntheticAttrChildNodes())
150 return nullptr;
151 ASSERT(attrNodeListMap().contains(&element));
152 return &attrNodeListMap().find(&element)->value;
153}
154
155static Vector<RefPtr<Attr>>& ensureAttrNodeListForElement(Element& element)
156{
157 if (element.hasSyntheticAttrChildNodes()) {
158 ASSERT(attrNodeListMap().contains(&element));
159 return attrNodeListMap().find(&element)->value;
160 }
161 ASSERT(!attrNodeListMap().contains(&element));
162 element.setHasSyntheticAttrChildNodes(true);
163 return attrNodeListMap().add(&element, Vector<RefPtr<Attr>>()).iterator->value;
164}
165
166static void removeAttrNodeListForElement(Element& element)
167{
168 ASSERT(element.hasSyntheticAttrChildNodes());
169 ASSERT(attrNodeListMap().contains(&element));
170 attrNodeListMap().remove(&element);
171 element.setHasSyntheticAttrChildNodes(false);
172}
173
174static Attr* findAttrNodeInList(Vector<RefPtr<Attr>>& attrNodeList, const QualifiedName& name)
175{
176 for (auto& node : attrNodeList) {
177 if (node->qualifiedName().matches(name))
178 return node.get();
179 }
180 return nullptr;
181}
182
183static Attr* findAttrNodeInList(Vector<RefPtr<Attr>>& attrNodeList, const AtomString& localName, bool shouldIgnoreAttributeCase)
184{
185 const AtomString& caseAdjustedName = shouldIgnoreAttributeCase ? localName.convertToASCIILowercase() : localName;
186 for (auto& node : attrNodeList) {
187 if (node->qualifiedName().localName() == caseAdjustedName)
188 return node.get();
189 }
190 return nullptr;
191}

204Element::~Element()
205{
206 ASSERT(!beforePseudoElement());
207 ASSERT(!afterPseudoElement());
208
209#if ENABLE(INTERSECTION_OBSERVER)
210 disconnectFromIntersectionObservers();
211#endif
212
213#if ENABLE(RESIZE_OBSERVER)
214 disconnectFromResizeObservers();
215#endif
216
217 removeShadowRoot();
218
219 if (hasSyntheticAttrChildNodes())
220 detachAllAttrNodesFromElement();
221
222#if ENABLE(CSS_TYPED_OM)
223 if (hasRareData()) {
224 if (auto* map = elementRareData()->attributeStyleMap())
225 map->clearElement();
226 }
227#endif
228
229 if (hasPendingResources()) {
230 document().accessSVGExtensions().removeElementFromPendingResources(*this);
231 ASSERT(!hasPendingResources());
232 }
233}

253void Element::setTabIndexExplicitly(std::optional<int> tabIndex)
254{
255 if (!tabIndex) {
256 setTabIndexState(TabIndexState::NotSet);
257 return;
258 }
259 setTabIndexState([this, value = tabIndex.value()]() {
260 switch (value) {
261 case 0:
262 return TabIndexState::Zero;
263 case -1:
264 return TabIndexState::NegativeOne;
265 default:
266 ensureElementRareData().setUnusualTabIndex(value);
267 return TabIndexState::InRareData;
268 }
269 }());
270}
271
272std::optional<int> Element::tabIndexSetExplicitly() const
273{
274 switch (tabIndexState()) {
275 case TabIndexState::NotSet:
276 return std::nullopt;
277 case TabIndexState::Zero:
278 return 0;
279 case TabIndexState::NegativeOne:
280 return -1;
281 case TabIndexState::InRareData:
282 ASSERT(hasRareData());
283 return elementRareData()->unusualTabIndex();
284 }
285 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
286 return std::nullopt;
287}

314bool Element::isKeyboardFocusable(KeyboardEvent*) const
315{
316 if (!(isFocusable() && !shouldBeIgnoredInSequentialFocusNavigation() && tabIndexSetExplicitly().value_or(0) >= 0))
317 return false;
318 if (auto* root = shadowRoot()) {
319 if (root->delegatesFocus())
320 return false;
321 }
322 return true;
323}

335static bool isForceEvent(const PlatformMouseEvent& platformEvent)
336{
337 return platformEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::MouseForceChanged || platformEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::MouseForceDown || platformEvent.type() == PlatformEvent::MouseForceUp;
338}
339
340static bool isCompatibilityMouseEvent(const MouseEvent& mouseEvent)
341{
342 // https://www.w3.org/TR/pointerevents/#compatibility-mapping-with-mouse-events
343 const auto& type = mouseEvent.type();
344 return type != eventNames().clickEvent && type != eventNames().mouseoverEvent && type != eventNames().mouseoutEvent && type != eventNames().mouseenterEvent && type != eventNames().mouseleaveEvent;
345}
346
347enum class ShouldIgnoreMouseEvent : bool { No, Yes };
348static ShouldIgnoreMouseEvent dispatchPointerEventIfNeeded(Element& element, const MouseEvent& mouseEvent, const PlatformMouseEvent& platformEvent, bool& didNotSwallowEvent)
349{
350 if (auto* page = element.document().page()) {
351 auto& pointerCaptureController = page->pointerCaptureController();
352#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
353 if (platformEvent.pointerId() != mousePointerID && mouseEvent.type() != eventNames().clickEvent && pointerCaptureController.preventsCompatibilityMouseEventsForIdentifier(platformEvent.pointerId()))
354 return ShouldIgnoreMouseEvent::Yes;
355#else
356 UNUSED_PARAM(platformEvent);
357#endif
358 if (platformEvent.syntheticClickType() != NoTap)
359 return ShouldIgnoreMouseEvent::No;
360
361 if (auto pointerEvent = pointerCaptureController.pointerEventForMouseEvent(mouseEvent, platformEvent.pointerId(), platformEvent.pointerType())) {
362 pointerCaptureController.dispatchEvent(*pointerEvent, &element);
363 if (isCompatibilityMouseEvent(mouseEvent) && pointerCaptureController.preventsCompatibilityMouseEventsForIdentifier(pointerEvent->pointerId()))
364 return ShouldIgnoreMouseEvent::Yes;
365 if (pointerEvent->defaultPrevented() || pointerEvent->defaultHandled()) {
366 didNotSwallowEvent = false;
367 if (pointerEvent->type() == eventNames().pointerdownEvent)
368 return ShouldIgnoreMouseEvent::Yes;
369 }
370 }
371 }
372
373 return ShouldIgnoreMouseEvent::No;
374}
375
376bool Element::dispatchMouseEvent(const PlatformMouseEvent& platformEvent, const AtomString& eventType, int detail, Element* relatedTarget, IsSyntheticClick isSyntheticClick)
377{
378 if (isDisabledFormControl())
379 return false;
380
381 if (isForceEvent(platformEvent) && !document().hasListenerTypeForEventType(platformEvent.type()))
382 return false;
383
384 Ref<MouseEvent> mouseEvent = MouseEvent::create(eventType, document().windowProxy(), platformEvent, detail, relatedTarget);
385
386 if (mouseEvent->type().isEmpty())
387 return true; // Shouldn't happen.
388
389 Ref protectedThis { *this };
390 bool didNotSwallowEvent = true;
391
392 if (dispatchPointerEventIfNeeded(*this, mouseEvent.get(), platformEvent, didNotSwallowEvent) == ShouldIgnoreMouseEvent::Yes)
393 return false;
394
395 auto isParentProcessAFullWebBrowser = false;
396#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
397 if (Frame* frame = document().frame())
398 isParentProcessAFullWebBrowser = frame->loader().client().isParentProcessAFullWebBrowser();
399#elif PLATFORM(MAC)
400 isParentProcessAFullWebBrowser = MacApplication::isSafari();
401#endif
402 if (Quirks::StorageAccessResult::ShouldCancelEvent == document().quirks().triggerOptionalStorageAccessQuirk(*this, platformEvent, eventType, detail, relatedTarget, isParentProcessAFullWebBrowser, isSyntheticClick))
403 return false;
404
405 ASSERT(!mouseEvent->target() || mouseEvent->target() != relatedTarget);
406 dispatchEvent(mouseEvent);
407 if (mouseEvent->defaultPrevented() || mouseEvent->defaultHandled())
408 didNotSwallowEvent = false;
409
410 if (mouseEvent->type() == eventNames().clickEvent && mouseEvent->detail() == 2) {
411 // Special case: If it's a double click event, we also send the dblclick event. This is not part
412 // of the DOM specs, but is used for compatibility with the ondblclick="" attribute. This is treated
413 // as a separate event in other DOM-compliant browsers like Firefox, and so we do the same.
414 // FIXME: Is it okay that mouseEvent may have been mutated by scripts via initMouseEvent in dispatchEvent above?
415 Ref<MouseEvent> doubleClickEvent = MouseEvent::create(eventNames().dblclickEvent,
416 mouseEvent->bubbles() ? Event::CanBubble::Yes : Event::CanBubble::No,
417 mouseEvent->cancelable() ? Event::IsCancelable::Yes : Event::IsCancelable::No,
418 Event::IsComposed::Yes,
419 mouseEvent->view(), mouseEvent->detail(),
420 mouseEvent->screenX(), mouseEvent->screenY(), mouseEvent->clientX(), mouseEvent->clientY(),
421 mouseEvent->modifierKeys(), mouseEvent->button(), mouseEvent->buttons(), mouseEvent->syntheticClickType(), relatedTarget);
422
423 if (mouseEvent->defaultHandled())
424 doubleClickEvent->setDefaultHandled();
425
426 dispatchEvent(doubleClickEvent);
427 if (doubleClickEvent->defaultHandled() || doubleClickEvent->defaultPrevented())
428 return false;
429 }
430 return didNotSwallowEvent;
431}

433bool Element::dispatchWheelEvent(const PlatformWheelEvent& platformEvent, OptionSet<EventHandling>& processing, Event::IsCancelable isCancelable)
434{
435 auto event = WheelEvent::create(platformEvent, document().windowProxy(), isCancelable);
436
437 // Events with no deltas are important because they convey platform information about scroll gestures
438 // and momentum beginning or ending. However, those events should not be sent to the DOM since some
439 // websites will break. They need to be dispatched because dispatching them will call into the default
440 // event handler, and our platform code will correctly handle the phase changes. Calling stopPropagation()
441 // will prevent the event from being sent to the DOM, but will still call the default event handler.
442 // FIXME: Move this logic into WheelEvent::create.
443 if (platformEvent.delta().isZero())
444 event->stopPropagation();
445 else
446 processing.add(EventHandling::DispatchedToDOM);
447
448 dispatchEvent(event);
449
450 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "Element " << *this << " dispatchWheelEvent: (cancelable " << event->cancelable() << ") defaultPrevented " << event->defaultPrevented() << " defaultHandled " << event->defaultHandled());
451
452 if (event->defaultPrevented())
453 processing.add(EventHandling::DefaultPrevented);
454
455 if (event->defaultHandled())
456 processing.add(EventHandling::DefaultHandled);
457
458 return !event->defaultPrevented() && !event->defaultHandled();
459}
460
461bool Element::dispatchKeyEvent(const PlatformKeyboardEvent& platformEvent)
462{
463 auto event = KeyboardEvent::create(platformEvent, document().windowProxy());
464
465 if (Frame* frame = document().frame()) {
466 if (frame->eventHandler().accessibilityPreventsEventPropagation(event))
467 event->stopPropagation();
468 }
469
470 dispatchEvent(event);
471 return !event->defaultPrevented() && !event->defaultHandled();
472}

479Ref<Node> Element::cloneNodeInternal(Document& targetDocument, CloningOperation type)
480{
481 switch (type) {
482 case CloningOperation::OnlySelf:
483 case CloningOperation::SelfWithTemplateContent:
484 return cloneElementWithoutChildren(targetDocument);
485 case CloningOperation::Everything:
486 break;
487 }
488 return cloneElementWithChildren(targetDocument);
489}
490
491Ref<Element> Element::cloneElementWithChildren(Document& targetDocument)
492{
493 Ref<Element> clone = cloneElementWithoutChildren(targetDocument);
494 cloneChildNodes(clone);
495 return clone;
496}
497
498Ref<Element> Element::cloneElementWithoutChildren(Document& targetDocument)
499{
500 Ref<Element> clone = cloneElementWithoutAttributesAndChildren(targetDocument);
501
502 // This will catch HTML elements in the wrong namespace that are not correctly copied.
503 // This is a sanity check as HTML overloads some of the DOM methods.
504 ASSERT(isHTMLElement() == clone->isHTMLElement());
505
506 clone->cloneDataFromElement(*this);
507 return clone;
508}
509
510Ref<Element> Element::cloneElementWithoutAttributesAndChildren(Document& targetDocument)
511{
512 return targetDocument.createElement(tagQName(), false);
513}

515Ref<Attr> Element::detachAttribute(unsigned index)
516{
517 ASSERT(elementData());
518
519 const Attribute& attribute = elementData()->attributeAt(index);
520
521 RefPtr<Attr> attrNode = attrIfExists(attribute.name());
522 if (attrNode)
523 detachAttrNodeFromElementWithValue(attrNode.get(), attribute.value());
524 else
525 attrNode = Attr::create(document(), attribute.name(), attribute.value());
526
527 removeAttributeInternal(index, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
528 return attrNode.releaseNonNull();
529}
530
531bool Element::removeAttribute(const QualifiedName& name)
532{
533 if (!elementData())
534 return false;
535
536 unsigned index = elementData()->findAttributeIndexByName(name);
537 if (index == ElementData::attributeNotFound)
538 return false;
539
540 removeAttributeInternal(index, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
541 return true;
542}
543
544void Element::setBooleanAttribute(const QualifiedName& name, bool value)
545{
546 if (value)
547 setAttribute(name, emptyAtom());
548 else
549 removeAttribute(name);
550}

572void Element::synchronizeAllAttributes() const
573{
574 if (!elementData())
575 return;
576 if (elementData()->styleAttributeIsDirty()) {
577 ASSERT(isStyledElement());
578 static_cast<const StyledElement*>(this)->synchronizeStyleAttributeInternal();
579 }
580
581 if (isSVGElement())
582 downcast<SVGElement>(const_cast<Element&>(*this)).synchronizeAllAttributes();
583}

585ALWAYS_INLINE void Element::synchronizeAttribute(const QualifiedName& name) const
586{
587 if (!elementData())
588 return;
589 if (UNLIKELY(name == styleAttr && elementData()->styleAttributeIsDirty())) {
590 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(isStyledElement());
591 static_cast<const StyledElement*>(this)->synchronizeStyleAttributeInternal();
592 return;
593 }
594
595 if (isSVGElement())
596 downcast<SVGElement>(const_cast<Element&>(*this)).synchronizeAttribute(name);
597}
598
599static ALWAYS_INLINE bool isStyleAttribute(const Element& element, const AtomString& attributeLocalName)
600{
601 if (shouldIgnoreAttributeCase(element))
602 return equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(attributeLocalName, "style");
603 return attributeLocalName == styleAttr->localName();
604}
605
606ALWAYS_INLINE void Element::synchronizeAttribute(const AtomString& localName) const
607{
608 // This version of synchronizeAttribute() is streamlined for the case where you don't have a full QualifiedName,
609 // e.g when called from DOM API.
610 if (!elementData())
611 return;
612 if (elementData()->styleAttributeIsDirty() && isStyleAttribute(*this, localName)) {
613 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(isStyledElement());
614 static_cast<const StyledElement*>(this)->synchronizeStyleAttributeInternal();
615 return;
616 }
617
618 if (isSVGElement())
619 downcast<SVGElement>(const_cast<Element&>(*this)).synchronizeAttribute(QualifiedName(nullAtom(), localName, nullAtom()));
620}
621
622const AtomString& Element::getAttribute(const QualifiedName& name) const
623{
624 if (!elementData())
625 return nullAtom();
626 synchronizeAttribute(name);
627 if (const Attribute* attribute = findAttributeByName(name))
628 return attribute->value();
629 return nullAtom();
630}
631
632Vector<String> Element::getAttributeNames() const
633{
634 Vector<String> attributesVector;
635 if (!hasAttributes())
636 return attributesVector;
637
638 auto attributes = attributesIterator();
639 attributesVector.reserveInitialCapacity(attributes.attributeCount());
640 for (auto& attribute : attributes)
641 attributesVector.uncheckedAppend(attribute.name().toString());
642 return attributesVector;
643}
644
645bool Element::isFocusable() const
646{
647 if (!isConnected() || !supportsFocus())
648 return false;
649
650 if (!renderer()) {
651 // Elements in canvas fallback content are not rendered, but they are allowed to be
652 // focusable as long as their canvas is displayed and visible.
653 if (auto* canvas = ancestorsOfType<HTMLCanvasElement>(*this).first())
654 return canvas->isVisibleWithoutResolvingFullStyle();
655 }
656
657 return isVisibleWithoutResolvingFullStyle();
658}

701
702void Element::setActive(bool flag, bool pause, Style::InvalidationScope invalidationScope)
703{
704 if (flag == active())
705 return;
706 {
707 Style::PseudoClassChangeInvalidation styleInvalidation(*this, CSSSelector::PseudoClassActive, invalidationScope);
708 document().userActionElements().setActive(*this, flag);
709 }
710
711 if (!renderer())
712 return;
713
714 bool reactsToPress = false;
715 if (renderer()->style().hasAppearance() && renderer()->theme().stateChanged(*renderer(), ControlStates::States::Pressed))
716 reactsToPress = true;
717
718 // The rest of this function implements a feature that only works if the
719 // platform supports immediate invalidations on the ChromeClient, so bail if
720 // that isn't supported.
721 if (!document().page()->chrome().client().supportsImmediateInvalidation())
722 return;
723
724 if (reactsToPress && pause) {
725 // The delay here is subtle. It relies on an assumption, namely that the amount of time it takes
726 // to repaint the "down" state of the control is about the same time as it would take to repaint the
727 // "up" state. Once you assume this, you can just delay for 100ms - that time (assuming that after you
728 // leave this method, it will be about that long before the flush of the up state happens again).
729#ifdef HAVE_FUNC_USLEEP
730 MonotonicTime startTime = MonotonicTime::now();
731#endif
732
733 document().updateStyleIfNeeded();
734
735 // Do an immediate repaint.
736 if (renderer())
737 renderer()->repaint();
738
739 // FIXME: Come up with a less ridiculous way of doing this.
740#ifdef HAVE_FUNC_USLEEP
741 // Now pause for a small amount of time (1/10th of a second from before we repainted in the pressed state)
742 Seconds remainingTime = 100_ms - (MonotonicTime::now() - startTime);
743 if (remainingTime > 0_s)
744 usleep(static_cast<useconds_t>(remainingTime.microseconds()));
745#endif
746 }
747}

749static bool shouldAlwaysHaveFocusVisibleWhenFocused(const Element& element)
750{
751 return element.isTextField() || element.isContentEditable();
752}
753
754void Element::setFocus(bool flag, FocusVisibility visibility)
755{
756 if (flag == focused())
757 return;
758 {
759 Style::PseudoClassChangeInvalidation focusStyleInvalidation(*this, CSSSelector::PseudoClassFocus);
760 Style::PseudoClassChangeInvalidation directFocusStyleInvalidation(*this, CSSSelector::PseudoClassDirectFocus);
761 document().userActionElements().setFocused(*this, flag);
762 }
763
764 // Shadow host with a slot that contain focused element is not considered focused.
765 for (auto* root = containingShadowRoot(); root; root = root->host()->containingShadowRoot()) {
766 root->setContainsFocusedElement(flag);
767 root->host()->invalidateStyle();
768 }
769
770 for (auto* element = this; element; element = element->parentElementInComposedTree())
771 element->setHasFocusWithin(flag);
772
773 setHasFocusVisible(flag && (visibility == FocusVisibility::Visible || shouldAlwaysHaveFocusVisibleWhenFocused(*this)));
774}
775
776void Element::setHasFocusVisible(bool flag)
777{
778 if (!document().settings().focusVisibleEnabled())

781#if ASSERT_ENABLED
782 ASSERT(!flag || focused());
783 ASSERT(!focused() || !shouldAlwaysHaveFocusVisibleWhenFocused(*this) || flag);
784#endif
785
786 if (hasFocusVisible() == flag)
787 return;
788
789 Style::PseudoClassChangeInvalidation styleInvalidation(*this, CSSSelector::PseudoClassFocusVisible);
790 document().userActionElements().setHasFocusVisible(*this, flag);
791}

825inline ScrollAlignment toScrollAlignmentForInlineDirection(std::optional<ScrollLogicalPosition> position, WritingMode writingMode, bool isLTR)
826{
827 switch (position.value_or(ScrollLogicalPosition::Nearest)) {
828 case ScrollLogicalPosition::Start: {
829 switch (writingMode) {
830 case WritingMode::TopToBottom:
831 case WritingMode::BottomToTop: {
832 return isLTR ? ScrollAlignment::alignLeftAlways : ScrollAlignment::alignRightAlways;
833 }
834 case WritingMode::LeftToRight:
835 case WritingMode::RightToLeft: {
836 return isLTR ? ScrollAlignment::alignTopAlways : ScrollAlignment::alignBottomAlways;
837 }
838 default:
839 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
840 return ScrollAlignment::alignLeftAlways;
841 }
842 }
843 case ScrollLogicalPosition::Center:
844 return ScrollAlignment::alignCenterAlways;
845 case ScrollLogicalPosition::End: {
846 switch (writingMode) {
847 case WritingMode::TopToBottom:
848 case WritingMode::BottomToTop: {
849 return isLTR ? ScrollAlignment::alignRightAlways : ScrollAlignment::alignLeftAlways;
850 }
851 case WritingMode::LeftToRight:
852 case WritingMode::RightToLeft: {
853 return isLTR ? ScrollAlignment::alignBottomAlways : ScrollAlignment::alignTopAlways;
854 }
855 default:
856 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
857 return ScrollAlignment::alignRightAlways;
858 }
859 }
860 case ScrollLogicalPosition::Nearest:
861 return ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded;
862 default:
863 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
864 return ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded;
865 }
866}
867
868inline ScrollAlignment toScrollAlignmentForBlockDirection(std::optional<ScrollLogicalPosition> position, WritingMode writingMode)
869{
870 switch (position.value_or(ScrollLogicalPosition::Start)) {
871 case ScrollLogicalPosition::Start: {
872 switch (writingMode) {
873 case WritingMode::TopToBottom:
874 return ScrollAlignment::alignTopAlways;
875 case WritingMode::BottomToTop:
876 return ScrollAlignment::alignBottomAlways;
877 case WritingMode::LeftToRight:
878 return ScrollAlignment::alignLeftAlways;
879 case WritingMode::RightToLeft:
880 return ScrollAlignment::alignRightAlways;
881 default:
882 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
883 return ScrollAlignment::alignTopAlways;
884 }
885 }
886 case ScrollLogicalPosition::Center:
887 return ScrollAlignment::alignCenterAlways;
888 case ScrollLogicalPosition::End: {
889 switch (writingMode) {
890 case WritingMode::TopToBottom:
891 return ScrollAlignment::alignBottomAlways;
892 case WritingMode::BottomToTop:
893 return ScrollAlignment::alignTopAlways;
894 case WritingMode::LeftToRight:
895 return ScrollAlignment::alignRightAlways;
896 case WritingMode::RightToLeft:
897 return ScrollAlignment::alignLeftAlways;
898 default:
899 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
900 return ScrollAlignment::alignBottomAlways;
901 }
902 }
903 case ScrollLogicalPosition::Nearest:
904 return ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded;
905 default:
906 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
907 return ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded;
908 }
909}

911void Element::scrollIntoView(std::optional<Variant<bool, ScrollIntoViewOptions>>&& arg)
912{
913 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
914
915 if (!renderer())
916 return;
917
918 bool insideFixed;
919 LayoutRect absoluteBounds = renderer()->absoluteAnchorRectWithScrollMargin(&insideFixed);
920
921 ScrollIntoViewOptions options;
922 if (arg) {
923 auto value = arg.value();
924 if (WTF::holds_alternative<ScrollIntoViewOptions>(value))
925 options = WTF::get<ScrollIntoViewOptions>(value);
926 else if (!WTF::get<bool>(value))
927 options.blockPosition = ScrollLogicalPosition::End;
928 }
929
930 auto writingMode = renderer()->style().writingMode();
931 ScrollAlignment alignX = toScrollAlignmentForInlineDirection(options.inlinePosition, writingMode, renderer()->style().isLeftToRightDirection());
932 ScrollAlignment alignY = toScrollAlignmentForBlockDirection(options.blockPosition, writingMode);
933
934 bool isHorizontal = renderer()->style().isHorizontalWritingMode();
935 ScrollRectToVisibleOptions visibleOptions {
936 SelectionRevealMode::Reveal,
937 isHorizontal ? alignX : alignY,
938 isHorizontal ? alignY : alignX,
939 ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::No,
940 options.behavior.value_or(ScrollBehavior::Auto),
941 SmoothScrollFeatureEnablement::Default
942 };
943 renderer()->scrollRectToVisible(absoluteBounds, insideFixed, visibleOptions);
944}
945
946void Element::scrollIntoView(bool alignToTop)
947{
948 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
949
950 if (!renderer())
951 return;
952
953 bool insideFixed;
954 LayoutRect absoluteBounds = renderer()->absoluteAnchorRectWithScrollMargin(&insideFixed);
955 // Align to the top / bottom and to the closest edge.
956 if (alignToTop)
957 renderer()->scrollRectToVisible(absoluteBounds, insideFixed, { SelectionRevealMode::Reveal, ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded, ScrollAlignment::alignTopAlways, ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::No });
958 else
959 renderer()->scrollRectToVisible(absoluteBounds, insideFixed, { SelectionRevealMode::Reveal, ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded, ScrollAlignment::alignBottomAlways, ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::No });
960}
961
962void Element::scrollIntoViewIfNeeded(bool centerIfNeeded)
963{
964 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
965
966 if (!renderer())
967 return;
968
969 bool insideFixed;
970 LayoutRect absoluteBounds = renderer()->absoluteAnchorRectWithScrollMargin(&insideFixed);
971 if (centerIfNeeded)
972 renderer()->scrollRectToVisible(absoluteBounds, insideFixed, { SelectionRevealMode::Reveal, ScrollAlignment::alignCenterIfNeeded, ScrollAlignment::alignCenterIfNeeded, ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::No });
973 else
974 renderer()->scrollRectToVisible(absoluteBounds, insideFixed, { SelectionRevealMode::Reveal, ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded, ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded, ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::No });
975}

988 else

992void Element::scrollBy(const ScrollToOptions& options)
993{
994 ScrollToOptions scrollToOptions = normalizeNonFiniteCoordinatesOrFallBackTo(options, 0, 0);
995 scrollToOptions.left.value() += scrollLeft();
996 scrollToOptions.top.value() += scrollTop();
997 scrollTo(scrollToOptions, ScrollClamping::Clamped, ScrollSnapPointSelectionMethod::Directional);
998}
999
1000void Element::scrollBy(double x, double y)
1001{
1002 scrollBy(ScrollToOptions(x, y));
1003}
1004
1005void Element::scrollTo(const ScrollToOptions& options, ScrollClamping clamping, ScrollSnapPointSelectionMethod snapPointSelectionMethod)
1006{
1007 if (!document().settings().CSSOMViewScrollingAPIEnabled()) {
1008 // If the element is the root element and document is in quirks mode, terminate these steps.
1009 // Note that WebKit always uses quirks mode document scrolling behavior. See Document::scrollingElement().
1010 if (this == document().documentElement())
1011 return;
1012 }
1013
1014 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1015
1016 if (document().scrollingElement() == this) {
1017 // If the element is the scrolling element and is not potentially scrollable,
1018 // invoke scroll() on window with options as the only argument, and terminate these steps.
1019 // FIXME: Scrolling an independently scrollable body is broken: webkit.org/b/161612.
1020 auto window = makeRefPtr(document().domWindow());
1021 if (!window)
1022 return;
1023
1024 window->scrollTo(options, clamping, snapPointSelectionMethod);
1025 return;
1026 }
1027
1028 // If the element does not have any associated CSS layout box, the element has no associated scrolling box,
1029 // or the element has no overflow, terminate these steps.
1030 RenderBox* renderer = renderBox();
1031 if (!renderer || !renderer->hasOverflowClip())
1032 return;
1033
1034 auto scrollToOptions = normalizeNonFiniteCoordinatesOrFallBackTo(options,
1035 adjustForAbsoluteZoom(renderer->scrollLeft(), *renderer),
1036 adjustForAbsoluteZoom(renderer->scrollTop(), *renderer)
1037 );
1038 IntPoint scrollPosition(
1039 clampToInteger(scrollToOptions.left.value() * renderer->style().effectiveZoom()),
1040 clampToInteger(scrollToOptions.top.value() * renderer->style().effectiveZoom())
1041 );
1042
1043 auto animated = useSmoothScrolling(scrollToOptions.behavior.value_or(ScrollBehavior::Auto), this) ? AnimatedScroll::Yes : AnimatedScroll::No;
1044 auto scrollPositionChangeOptions = ScrollPositionChangeOptions::createProgrammaticWithOptions(clamping, animated, snapPointSelectionMethod);
1045 renderer->setScrollPosition(scrollPosition, scrollPositionChangeOptions);
1046}
1047
1048void Element::scrollTo(double x, double y)
1049{
1050 scrollTo(ScrollToOptions(x, y));
1051}
1052
1053void Element::scrollByUnits(int units, ScrollGranularity granularity)
1054{
1055 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1056
1057 auto* renderer = this->renderer();
1058 if (!renderer)
1059 return;
1060
1061 if (!renderer->hasOverflowClip())
1062 return;
1063
1064 ScrollDirection direction = ScrollDown;
1065 if (units < 0) {
1066 direction = ScrollUp;
1067 units = -units;
1068 }
1069 Element* stopElement = this;
1070 downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer).scroll(direction, granularity, units, &stopElement);
1071}

1078void Element::scrollByPages(int pages)

1080 scrollByUnits(pages, ScrollByPage);
1081}

1083static double localZoomForRenderer(const RenderElement& renderer)
1084{
1085 // FIXME: This does the wrong thing if two opposing zooms are in effect and canceled each
1086 // other out, but the alternative is that we'd have to crawl up the whole render tree every
1087 // time (or store an additional bit in the RenderStyle to indicate that a zoom was specified).
1088 double zoomFactor = 1;
1089 if (renderer.style().effectiveZoom() != 1) {
1090 // Need to find the nearest enclosing RenderElement that set up
1091 // a differing zoom, and then we divide our result by it to eliminate the zoom.
1092 const RenderElement* prev = &renderer;
1093 for (RenderElement* curr = prev->parent(); curr; curr = curr->parent()) {
1094 if (curr->style().effectiveZoom() != prev->style().effectiveZoom()) {
1095 zoomFactor = prev->style().zoom();
1096 break;
1097 }
1098 prev = curr;
1099 }
1100 if (prev->isRenderView())
1101 zoomFactor = prev->style().zoom();
1102 }
1103 return zoomFactor;
1104}
1105
1106static int adjustContentsScrollPositionOrSizeForZoom(int value, const Frame& frame)
1107{
1108 double zoomFactor = frame.pageZoomFactor() * frame.frameScaleFactor();
1109 if (zoomFactor == 1)
1110 return value;
1111 // FIXME (webkit.org/b/189397): Why can't we just ceil/floor?
1112 // Needed because of truncation (rather than rounding) when scaling up.
1113 if (zoomFactor > 1)
1114 value++;
1115 return static_cast<int>(value / zoomFactor);
1116}
1117
1118enum LegacyCSSOMElementMetricsRoundingStrategy { Round, Floor };
1119
1120static int convertToNonSubpixelValue(double value, const LegacyCSSOMElementMetricsRoundingStrategy roundStrategy = Round)
1121{
1122 return roundStrategy == Round ? std::round(value) : std::floor(value);
1123}
1124
1125static int adjustOffsetForZoomAndSubpixelLayout(RenderBoxModelObject& renderer, const LayoutUnit& offset)
1126{
1127 auto offsetLeft = LayoutUnit { roundToInt(offset) };
1128 double zoomFactor = localZoomForRenderer(renderer);
1129 if (zoomFactor == 1)
1130 return convertToNonSubpixelValue(offsetLeft, Floor);
1131 return convertToNonSubpixelValue(offsetLeft / zoomFactor, Round);
1132}

1134static HashSet<TreeScope*> collectAncestorTreeScopeAsHashSet(Node& node)
1135{
1136 HashSet<TreeScope*> ancestors;
1137 for (auto* currentScope = &node.treeScope(); currentScope; currentScope = currentScope->parentTreeScope())
1138 ancestors.add(currentScope);
1139 return ancestors;
1140}

1142int Element::offsetLeftForBindings()
1143{
1144 auto offset = offsetLeft();
1145
1146 auto parent = makeRefPtr(offsetParent());
1147 if (!parent || !parent->isInShadowTree())
1148 return offset;
1149
1150 ASSERT(&parent->document() == &document());
1151 if (&parent->treeScope() == &treeScope())
1152 return offset;
1153
1154 auto ancestorTreeScopes = collectAncestorTreeScopeAsHashSet(*this);
1155 while (parent && !ancestorTreeScopes.contains(&parent->treeScope())) {
1156 offset += parent->offsetLeft();
1157 parent = parent->offsetParent();
1158 }
1159
1160 return offset;
1161}

1164{
1165 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1166 if (RenderBoxModelObject* renderer = renderBoxModelObject())
1167 return adjustOffsetForZoomAndSubpixelLayout(*renderer, renderer->offsetLeft());
1168 return 0;
1169}

1263
1264int Element::clientWidth()
1265{
1266 document().updateLayoutIfDimensionsOutOfDate(*this, WidthDimensionsCheck);
1267
1268 if (!document().hasLivingRenderTree())
1269 return 0;
1270
1271 RenderView& renderView = *document().renderView();
1272
1273 // When in strict mode, clientWidth for the document element should return the width of the containing frame.
1274 // When in quirks mode, clientWidth for the body element should return the width of the containing frame.
1275 bool inQuirksMode = document().inQuirksMode();
1276 if ((!inQuirksMode && document().documentElement() == this) || (inQuirksMode && isHTMLElement() && document().bodyOrFrameset() == this))
1277 return adjustForAbsoluteZoom(renderView.frameView().layoutWidth(), renderView);
1278
1279 if (RenderBox* renderer = renderBox()) {
1280 auto clientWidth = LayoutUnit { roundToInt(renderer->clientWidth()) };
1281 // clientWidth/Height is the visual portion of the box content, not including
1282 // borders or scroll bars, but includes padding. And per
1283 // https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/tables.html#model,
1284 // table wrapper box is a principal block box that contains the table box
1285 // itself and any caption boxes, and table grid box is a block-level box that
1286 // contains the table's internal table boxes. When table's border is specified
1287 // in CSS, the border is added to table grid box, not table wrapper box.
1288 // Currently, WebKit doesn't have table wrapper box, and we are supposed to
1289 // retrieve clientWidth/Height from table wrapper box, not table grid box. So
1290 // when we retrieve clientWidth/Height, it includes table's border size.
1291 if (renderer->isTable())
1292 clientWidth += renderer->borderLeft() + renderer->borderRight();
1293 return convertToNonSubpixelValue(adjustLayoutUnitForAbsoluteZoom(clientWidth, *renderer).toDouble());
1294 }
1295 return 0;
1296}
1297
1298int Element::clientHeight()
1299{
1300 document().updateLayoutIfDimensionsOutOfDate(*this, HeightDimensionsCheck);
1301 if (!document().hasLivingRenderTree())
1302 return 0;
1303
1304 RenderView& renderView = *document().renderView();
1305
1306 // When in strict mode, clientHeight for the document element should return the height of the containing frame.
1307 // When in quirks mode, clientHeight for the body element should return the height of the containing frame.
1308 bool inQuirksMode = document().inQuirksMode();
1309 if ((!inQuirksMode && document().documentElement() == this) || (inQuirksMode && isHTMLElement() && document().bodyOrFrameset() == this))
1310 return adjustForAbsoluteZoom(renderView.frameView().layoutHeight(), renderView);
1311
1312 if (RenderBox* renderer = renderBox()) {
1313 auto clientHeight = LayoutUnit { roundToInt(renderer->clientHeight()) };
1314 // clientWidth/Height is the visual portion of the box content, not including
1315 // borders or scroll bars, but includes padding. And per
1316 // https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/tables.html#model,
1317 // table wrapper box is a principal block box that contains the table box
1318 // itself and any caption boxes, and table grid box is a block-level box that
1319 // contains the table's internal table boxes. When table's border is specified
1320 // in CSS, the border is added to table grid box, not table wrapper box.
1321 // Currently, WebKit doesn't have table wrapper box, and we are supposed to
1322 // retrieve clientWidth/Height from table wrapper box, not table grid box. So
1323 // when we retrieve clientWidth/Height, it includes table's border size.
1324 if (renderer->isTable())
1325 clientHeight += renderer->borderTop() + renderer->borderBottom();
1326 return convertToNonSubpixelValue(adjustLayoutUnitForAbsoluteZoom(clientHeight, *renderer).toDouble());
1327 }
1328 return 0;
1329}

1367void Element::setScrollLeft(int newLeft)
1368{
1369 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1370
1371 auto options = ScrollPositionChangeOptions::createProgrammatic();
1372 options.animated = useSmoothScrolling(ScrollBehavior::Auto, this) ? AnimatedScroll::Yes : AnimatedScroll::No;
1373
1374 if (document().scrollingElement() == this) {
1375 if (auto* frame = documentFrameWithNonNullView()) {
1376 IntPoint position(static_cast<int>(newLeft * frame->pageZoomFactor() * frame->frameScaleFactor()), frame->view()->scrollY());
1377 frame->view()->setScrollPosition(position, options);
1378 }
1379 return;
1380 }
1381
1382 if (auto* renderer = renderBox()) {
1383 int clampedLeft = clampToInteger(newLeft * renderer->style().effectiveZoom());
1384 renderer->setScrollLeft(clampedLeft, options);
1385 if (auto* scrollableArea = renderer->layer() ? renderer->layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr)
1386 scrollableArea->setScrollShouldClearLatchedState(true);
1387 }
1388}
1389
1390void Element::setScrollTop(int newTop)
1391{
1392 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1393
1394 auto options = ScrollPositionChangeOptions::createProgrammatic();
1395 options.animated = useSmoothScrolling(ScrollBehavior::Auto, this) ? AnimatedScroll::Yes : AnimatedScroll::No;
1396
1397 if (document().scrollingElement() == this) {
1398 if (auto* frame = documentFrameWithNonNullView()) {
1399 IntPoint position(frame->view()->scrollX(), static_cast<int>(newTop * frame->pageZoomFactor() * frame->frameScaleFactor()));
1400 frame->view()->setScrollPosition(position, options);
1401 }
1402 return;
1403 }
1404
1405 if (auto* renderer = renderBox()) {
1406 int clampedTop = clampToInteger(newTop * renderer->style().effectiveZoom());
1407 renderer->setScrollTop(clampedTop, options);
1408 if (auto* scrollableArea = renderer->layer() ? renderer->layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr)
1409 scrollableArea->setScrollShouldClearLatchedState(true);
1410 }
1411}

1413int Element::scrollWidth()
1414{
1415 document().updateLayoutIfDimensionsOutOfDate(*this, WidthDimensionsCheck);
1416
1417 if (document().scrollingElement() == this) {
1418 // FIXME (webkit.org/b/182289): updateLayoutIfDimensionsOutOfDate seems to ignore zoom level change.
1419 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1420 if (auto* frame = documentFrameWithNonNullView())
1421 return adjustContentsScrollPositionOrSizeForZoom(frame->view()->contentsWidth(), *frame);
1422 return 0;
1423 }
1424
1425 if (auto* renderer = renderBox())
1426 return adjustForAbsoluteZoom(renderer->scrollWidth(), *renderer);
1427 return 0;
1428}

1447IntRect Element::boundsInRootViewSpace()
1448{
1449 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1450
1451 FrameView* view = document().view();
1452 if (!view)
1453 return IntRect();
1454
1455 Vector<FloatQuad> quads;
1456
1457 if (isSVGElement() && renderer()) {
1458 // Get the bounding rectangle from the SVG model.
1459 SVGElement& svgElement = downcast<SVGElement>(*this);
1460 if (auto localRect = svgElement.getBoundingBox())
1461 quads.append(renderer()->localToAbsoluteQuad(*localRect));
1462 } else {
1463 // Get the bounding rectangle from the box model.
1464 if (renderBoxModelObject())
1465 renderBoxModelObject()->absoluteQuads(quads);
1466 }
1467
1468 return view->contentsToRootView(enclosingIntRect(unitedBoundingBoxes(quads)));
1469}
1470
1471static bool layoutOverflowRectContainsAllDescendants(const RenderBox& renderBox)
1472{
1473 if (renderBox.isRenderView())
1474 return true;
1475
1476 if (!renderBox.element())
1477 return false;
1478
1479 // If there are any position:fixed inside of us, game over.
1480 if (auto* viewPositionedObjects = renderBox.view().positionedObjects()) {
1481 for (auto* positionedBox : *viewPositionedObjects) {
1482 if (positionedBox == &renderBox)
1483 continue;
1484 if (positionedBox->isFixedPositioned() && renderBox.element()->contains(positionedBox->element()))
1485 return false;
1486 }
1487 }
1488
1489 if (renderBox.canContainAbsolutelyPositionedObjects()) {
1490 // Our layout overflow will include all descendant positioned elements.
1491 return true;
1492 }
1493
1494 // This renderer may have positioned descendants whose containing block is some ancestor.
1495 if (auto* containingBlock = renderBox.containingBlockForAbsolutePosition()) {
1496 if (auto* positionedObjects = containingBlock->positionedObjects()) {
1497 for (auto* positionedBox : *positionedObjects) {
1498 if (positionedBox == &renderBox)
1499 continue;
1500 if (renderBox.element()->contains(positionedBox->element()))
1501 return false;
1502 }
1503 }
1504 }
1505 return false;
1506}
1507
1508LayoutRect Element::absoluteEventBounds(bool& boundsIncludeAllDescendantElements, bool& includesFixedPositionElements)
1509{
1510 boundsIncludeAllDescendantElements = false;
1511 includesFixedPositionElements = false;
1512
1513 if (!renderer())
1514 return LayoutRect();
1515
1516 LayoutRect result;
1517 if (isSVGElement()) {
1518 // Get the bounding rectangle from the SVG model.
1519 SVGElement& svgElement = downcast<SVGElement>(*this);
1520 if (auto localRect = svgElement.getBoundingBox())
1521 result = LayoutRect(renderer()->localToAbsoluteQuad(*localRect, UseTransforms, &includesFixedPositionElements).boundingBox());
1522 } else {
1523 auto* renderer = this->renderer();
1524 if (is<RenderBox>(renderer)) {
1525 auto& box = downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer);
1526
1527 bool computedBounds = false;
1528
1529 if (RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = box.enclosingFragmentedFlow()) {
1530 bool wasFixed = false;
1531 Vector<FloatQuad> quads;
1532 FloatRect localRect(0, 0, box.width(), box.height());
1533 if (fragmentedFlow->absoluteQuadsForBox(quads, &wasFixed, &box, localRect.y(), localRect.maxY())) {
1534 result = LayoutRect(unitedBoundingBoxes(quads));
1535 computedBounds = true;
1536 } else {
1537 // Probably columns. Just return the bounds of the multicol block for now.
1538 // FIXME: this doesn't handle nested columns.
1539 RenderElement* multicolContainer = fragmentedFlow->parent();
1540 if (multicolContainer && is<RenderBox>(multicolContainer)) {
1541 auto overflowRect = downcast<RenderBox>(*multicolContainer).layoutOverflowRect();
1542 result = LayoutRect(multicolContainer->localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatRect(overflowRect), UseTransforms, &includesFixedPositionElements).boundingBox());
1543 computedBounds = true;
1544 }
1545 }
1546 }
1547
1548 if (!computedBounds) {
1549 LayoutRect overflowRect = box.layoutOverflowRect();
1550 result = LayoutRect(box.localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatRect(overflowRect), UseTransforms, &includesFixedPositionElements).boundingBox());
1551 boundsIncludeAllDescendantElements = layoutOverflowRectContainsAllDescendants(box);
1552 }
1553 } else
1554 result = LayoutRect(renderer->absoluteBoundingBoxRect(true /* useTransforms */, &includesFixedPositionElements));
1555 }
1556
1557 return result;
1558}
1559
1560LayoutRect Element::absoluteEventBoundsOfElementAndDescendants(bool& includesFixedPositionElements)
1561{
1562 bool boundsIncludeDescendants;
1563 LayoutRect result = absoluteEventBounds(boundsIncludeDescendants, includesFixedPositionElements);
1564 if (boundsIncludeDescendants)
1565 return result;
1566
1567 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<Element>(*this)) {
1568 bool includesFixedPosition = false;
1569 LayoutRect childBounds = child.absoluteEventBoundsOfElementAndDescendants(includesFixedPosition);
1570 includesFixedPositionElements |= includesFixedPosition;
1571 result.unite(childBounds);
1572 }
1573
1574 return result;
1575}
1576
1577LayoutRect Element::absoluteEventHandlerBounds(bool& includesFixedPositionElements)
1578{
1579 // This is not web-exposed, so don't call the FOUC-inducing updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets().
1580 FrameView* frameView = document().view();
1581 if (!frameView)
1582 return LayoutRect();
1583
1584 return absoluteEventBoundsOfElementAndDescendants(includesFixedPositionElements);
1585}

1587static std::optional<std::pair<RenderObject*, LayoutRect>> listBoxElementBoundingBox(Element& element)
1588{
1589 HTMLSelectElement* selectElement;
1590 bool isGroup;
1591 if (is<HTMLOptionElement>(element)) {
1592 selectElement = downcast<HTMLOptionElement>(element).ownerSelectElement();
1593 isGroup = false;
1594 } else if (is<HTMLOptGroupElement>(element)) {
1595 selectElement = downcast<HTMLOptGroupElement>(element).ownerSelectElement();
1596 isGroup = true;
1597 } else
1598 return std::nullopt;
1599
1600 if (!selectElement || !selectElement->renderer() || !is<RenderListBox>(selectElement->renderer()))
1601 return std::nullopt;
1602
1603 auto& renderer = downcast<RenderListBox>(*selectElement->renderer());
1604 std::optional<LayoutRect> boundingBox;
1605 int optionIndex = 0;
1606 for (auto* item : selectElement->listItems()) {
1607 if (item == &element) {
1608 LayoutPoint additionOffset;
1609 boundingBox = renderer.itemBoundingBoxRect(additionOffset, optionIndex);
1610 if (!isGroup)
1611 break;
1612 } else if (isGroup && boundingBox) {
1613 if (item->parentNode() != &element)
1614 break;
1615 LayoutPoint additionOffset;
1616 boundingBox->setHeight(boundingBox->height() + renderer.itemBoundingBoxRect(additionOffset, optionIndex).height());
1617 }
1618 ++optionIndex;
1619 }
1620
1621 if (!boundingBox)
1622 return std::nullopt;
1623
1624 return std::pair<RenderObject*, LayoutRect> { &renderer, boundingBox.value() };
1625}

1627Ref<DOMRectList> Element::getClientRects()
1628{
1629 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1630
1631 RenderObject* renderer = this->renderer();
1632 Vector<FloatQuad> quads;
1633
1634 if (auto pair = listBoxElementBoundingBox(*this)) {
1635 renderer = pair.value().first;
1636 quads.append(renderer->localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatQuad { pair.value().second }));
1637 } else if (auto* renderBoxModelObject = this->renderBoxModelObject())
1638 renderBoxModelObject->absoluteQuads(quads);
1639
1640 // FIXME: Handle SVG elements.
1641 // FIXME: Handle table/inline-table with a caption.
1642
1643 if (quads.isEmpty())
1644 return DOMRectList::create();
1645
1646 document().convertAbsoluteToClientQuads(quads, renderer->style());
1647 return DOMRectList::create(quads);
1648}

1650std::optional<std::pair<RenderObject*, FloatRect>> Element::boundingAbsoluteRectWithoutLayout()
1651{
1652 RenderObject* renderer = this->renderer();
1653 Vector<FloatQuad> quads;
1654 if (isSVGElement() && renderer && !renderer->isSVGRoot()) {
1655 // Get the bounding rectangle from the SVG model.
1656 SVGElement& svgElement = downcast<SVGElement>(*this);
1657 if (auto localRect = svgElement.getBoundingBox())
1658 quads.append(renderer->localToAbsoluteQuad(*localRect));

1718// https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#dom-element-toggleattribute
1719ExceptionOr<bool> Element::toggleAttribute(const AtomString& qualifiedName, std::optional<bool> force)
1720{
1721 if (!Document::isValidName(qualifiedName))
1722 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
1723
1724 synchronizeAttribute(qualifiedName);
1725
1726 auto caseAdjustedQualifiedName = shouldIgnoreAttributeCase(*this) ? qualifiedName.convertToASCIILowercase() : qualifiedName;
1727 unsigned index = elementData() ? elementData()->findAttributeIndexByName(caseAdjustedQualifiedName, false) : ElementData::attributeNotFound;
1728 if (index == ElementData::attributeNotFound) {
1729 if (!force || *force) {
1730 setAttributeInternal(index, QualifiedName { nullAtom(), caseAdjustedQualifiedName, nullAtom() }, emptyString(), NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
1731 return true;
1732 }
1733 return false;
1734 }
1735
1736 if (!force || !*force) {
1737 removeAttributeInternal(index, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
1738 return false;
1739 }
1740 return true;
1741}
1742
1743ExceptionOr<void> Element::setAttribute(const AtomString& qualifiedName, const AtomString& value)
1744{
1745 if (!Document::isValidName(qualifiedName))
1746 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
1747
1748 synchronizeAttribute(qualifiedName);
1749 auto caseAdjustedQualifiedName = shouldIgnoreAttributeCase(*this) ? qualifiedName.convertToASCIILowercase() : qualifiedName;
1750 unsigned index = elementData() ? elementData()->findAttributeIndexByName(caseAdjustedQualifiedName, false) : ElementData::attributeNotFound;
1751 auto name = index != ElementData::attributeNotFound ? attributeAt(index).name() : QualifiedName { nullAtom(), caseAdjustedQualifiedName, nullAtom() };
1752 setAttributeInternal(index, name, value, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
1753
1754 return { };
1755}

1761 setAttributeInternal(index, name, value, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
1762}

1775
1776inline void Element::setAttributeInternal(unsigned index, const QualifiedName& name, const AtomString& newValue, SynchronizationOfLazyAttribute inSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute)
1777{
1778 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(refCount() || parentNode(), "Attribute must not be set on an element before adoptRef");
1779
1780 if (newValue.isNull()) {
1781 if (index != ElementData::attributeNotFound)
1782 removeAttributeInternal(index, inSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
1783 return;
1784 }
1785
1786 if (index == ElementData::attributeNotFound) {
1787 addAttributeInternal(name, newValue, inSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
1788 return;
1789 }
1790
1791 if (inSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute) {
1792 ensureUniqueElementData().attributeAt(index).setValue(newValue);
1793 return;
1794 }
1795
1796 const Attribute& attribute = attributeAt(index);
1797 QualifiedName attributeName = attribute.name();
1798 AtomString oldValue = attribute.value();
1799
1800 willModifyAttribute(attributeName, oldValue, newValue);
1801
1802 if (newValue != oldValue) {
1803 Style::AttributeChangeInvalidation styleInvalidation(*this, name, oldValue, newValue);
1804 ensureUniqueElementData().attributeAt(index).setValue(newValue);
1805 }
1806
1807 didModifyAttribute(attributeName, oldValue, newValue);
1808}

1810static inline AtomString makeIdForStyleResolution(const AtomString& value, bool inQuirksMode)
1811{
1812 if (inQuirksMode)
1813 return value.convertToASCIILowercase();
1814 return value;
1815}
1816
1817void Element::attributeChanged(const QualifiedName& name, const AtomString& oldValue, const AtomString& newValue, AttributeModificationReason)
1818{
1819 bool valueIsSameAsBefore = oldValue == newValue;
1820
1821 if (!valueIsSameAsBefore) {
1822 if (name == HTMLNames::accesskeyAttr)
1823 document().invalidateAccessKeyCache();
1824 else if (name == HTMLNames::classAttr)
1825 classAttributeChanged(newValue);
1826 else if (name == HTMLNames::idAttr) {
1827 AtomString oldId = elementData()->idForStyleResolution();
1828 AtomString newId = makeIdForStyleResolution(newValue, document().inQuirksMode());
1829 if (newId != oldId) {
1830 Style::IdChangeInvalidation styleInvalidation(*this, oldId, newId);
1831 elementData()->setIdForStyleResolution(newId);
1832 }
1833
1834 if (!oldValue.isEmpty())
1835 treeScope().idTargetObserverRegistry().notifyObservers(*oldValue.impl());
1836 if (!newValue.isEmpty())
1837 treeScope().idTargetObserverRegistry().notifyObservers(*newValue.impl());
1838 } else if (name == HTMLNames::nameAttr)
1839 elementData()->setHasNameAttribute(!newValue.isNull());
1840 else if (name == HTMLNames::pseudoAttr) {
1841 if (needsStyleInvalidation() && isInShadowTree())
1842 invalidateStyleForSubtree();
1843 } else if (name == HTMLNames::slotAttr) {
1844 if (auto* parent = parentElement()) {
1845 if (auto* shadowRoot = parent->shadowRoot())
1846 shadowRoot->hostChildElementDidChangeSlotAttribute(*this, oldValue, newValue);
1847 }
1848 } else if (name == HTMLNames::partAttr)
1849 partAttributeChanged(newValue);
1850 else if (name == HTMLNames::exportpartsAttr) {
1851 if (auto* shadowRoot = this->shadowRoot()) {
1852 shadowRoot->invalidatePartMappings();
1853 Style::Invalidator::invalidateShadowParts(*shadowRoot);
1854 }
1855 }
1856 }
1857
1858 parseAttribute(name, newValue);
1859
1860 document().incDOMTreeVersion();
1861
1862 if (UNLIKELY(isDefinedCustomElement()))
1863 CustomElementReactionQueue::enqueueAttributeChangedCallbackIfNeeded(*this, name, oldValue, newValue);
1864
1865 if (valueIsSameAsBefore)
1866 return;
1867
1868 invalidateNodeListAndCollectionCachesInAncestorsForAttribute(name);
1869
1870 if (AXObjectCache* cache = document().existingAXObjectCache())
1871 cache->deferAttributeChangeIfNeeded(name, this);
1872}

1874template <typename CharacterType>
1875static inline bool isNonEmptyTokenList(const CharacterType* characters, unsigned length)
1876{
1877 ASSERT(length > 0);
1878
1879 unsigned i = 0;
1880 do {
1881 if (isNotHTMLSpace(characters[i]))
1882 break;
1883 ++i;
1884 } while (i < length);
1885
1886 return i < length;
1887}
1888
1889static inline bool isNonEmptyTokenList(const AtomString& stringValue)
1890{
1891 unsigned length = stringValue.length();
1892
1893 if (!length)
1894 return false;
1895
1896 if (stringValue.is8Bit())
1897 return isNonEmptyTokenList(stringValue.characters8(), length);
1898 return isNonEmptyTokenList(stringValue.characters16(), length);
1899}
1900
1901void Element::classAttributeChanged(const AtomString& newClassString)
1902{
1903 // Note: We'll need ElementData, but it doesn't have to be UniqueElementData.
1904 if (!elementData())
1905 ensureUniqueElementData();
1906
1907 bool shouldFoldCase = document().inQuirksMode();
1908 bool newStringHasClasses = isNonEmptyTokenList(newClassString);
1909
1910 auto oldClassNames = elementData()->classNames();
1911 auto newClassNames = newStringHasClasses ? SpaceSplitString(newClassString, shouldFoldCase) : SpaceSplitString();
1912 {
1913 Style::ClassChangeInvalidation styleInvalidation(*this, oldClassNames, newClassNames);
1914 elementData()->setClassNames(newClassNames);
1915 }
1916
1917 if (hasRareData()) {
1918 if (auto* classList = elementRareData()->classList())
1919 classList->associatedAttributeValueChanged(newClassString);
1920 }
1921}
1922
1923void Element::partAttributeChanged(const AtomString& newValue)
1924{
1925 bool hasParts = isNonEmptyTokenList(newValue);
1926 if (hasParts || !partNames().isEmpty()) {
1927 auto newParts = hasParts ? SpaceSplitString(newValue, false) : SpaceSplitString();
1928 ensureElementRareData().setPartNames(WTFMove(newParts));
1929 }
1930
1931 if (hasRareData()) {
1932 if (auto* partList = elementRareData()->partList())
1933 partList->associatedAttributeValueChanged(newValue);
1934 }
1935
1936 if (needsStyleInvalidation() && isInShadowTree())
1937 invalidateStyleInternal();
1938}

1940URL Element::absoluteLinkURL() const
1941{

1943 return URL();
1944
1945 AtomString linkAttribute;
1946 if (hasTagName(SVGNames::aTag))
1947 linkAttribute = getAttribute(SVGNames::hrefAttr, XLinkNames::hrefAttr);

1950

1952 return URL();

1955}

1983static void invalidateForSiblingCombinators(Element* sibling)
1984{
1985 for (; sibling; sibling = sibling->nextElementSibling()) {
1986 if (sibling->styleIsAffectedByPreviousSibling())
1987 sibling->invalidateStyleInternal();
1988 if (sibling->descendantsAffectedByPreviousSibling()) {
1989 for (auto* siblingChild = sibling->firstElementChild(); siblingChild; siblingChild = siblingChild->nextElementSibling())
1990 siblingChild->invalidateStyleForSubtreeInternal();
1991 }
1992 if (!sibling->affectsNextSiblingElementStyle())
1993 return;
1994 }
1995}

1997static void invalidateSiblingsIfNeeded(Element& element)
1998{
1999 if (!element.affectsNextSiblingElementStyle())
2000 return;
2001 auto* parent = element.parentElement();
2002 if (parent && parent->styleValidity() >= Style::Validity::SubtreeInvalid)
2003 return;
2004
2005 invalidateForSiblingCombinators(element.nextElementSibling());
2006}

2065// Returns true is the given attribute is an event handler.
2066// We consider an event handler any attribute that begins with "on".
2067// It is a simple solution that has the advantage of not requiring any
2068// code or configuration change if a new event handler is defined.
2069
2070bool Element::isEventHandlerAttribute(const Attribute& attribute) const
2071{

2195Node::InsertedIntoAncestorResult Element::insertedIntoAncestor(InsertionType insertionType, ContainerNode& parentOfInsertedTree)
2196{
2197 ContainerNode::insertedIntoAncestor(insertionType, parentOfInsertedTree);
2198
2199#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
2200 if (containsFullScreenElement() && parentElement() && !parentElement()->containsFullScreenElement())
2201 setContainsFullScreenElementOnAncestorsCrossingFrameBoundaries(true);
2202#endif
2203
2204 if (parentNode() == &parentOfInsertedTree) {
2205 if (auto* shadowRoot = parentNode()->shadowRoot())
2206 shadowRoot->hostChildElementDidChange(*this);
2207 }
2208
2209 if (!parentOfInsertedTree.isInTreeScope())
2210 return InsertedIntoAncestorResult::Done;
2211
2212 bool becomeConnected = insertionType.connectedToDocument;
2213 TreeScope* newScope = &parentOfInsertedTree.treeScope();
2214 HTMLDocument* newDocument = becomeConnected && is<HTMLDocument>(newScope->documentScope()) ? &downcast<HTMLDocument>(newScope->documentScope()) : nullptr;
2215 if (!insertionType.treeScopeChanged)
2216 newScope = nullptr;

2220 if (newScope)

2227 if (!nameValue.isNull()) {

2229 updateNameForTreeScope(*newScope, nullAtom(), nameValue);
2230 if (newDocument)
2231 updateNameForDocument(*newDocument, nullAtom(), nameValue);
2232 }
2233
2234 if (newScope && hasTagName(labelTag)) {
2235 if (newScope->shouldCacheLabelsByForAttribute())
2236 updateLabel(*newScope, nullAtom(), attributeWithoutSynchronization(forAttr));
2237 }
2238
2239 if (becomeConnected) {
2240 if (UNLIKELY(isCustomElementUpgradeCandidate())) {
2241 ASSERT(isConnected());
2242 CustomElementReactionQueue::tryToUpgradeElement(*this);
2243 }
2244 if (UNLIKELY(isDefinedCustomElement()))

2246 }

2249 newDocument->registerArticleElement(*this);
2250
2251 return InsertedIntoAncestorResult::Done;
2252}

2344{

2397 &asideTag.get(),
2398 &blockquoteTag.get(),
2399 &bodyTag.get(),
2400 &divTag.get(),
2401 &footerTag.get(),
2402 &h1Tag.get(),

2404 &h3Tag.get(),

2406 &h5Tag.get(),
2407 &h6Tag.get(),
2408 &headerTag.get(),

2410 &navTag.get(),

2412 &sectionTag.get(),

2414 };

2581static void invalidateForForwardPositionalRules(Element& parent, Element* elementAfterChange)
2582{
2583 bool childrenAffected = parent.childrenAffectedByForwardPositionalRules();
2584 bool descendantsAffected = parent.descendantsAffectedByForwardPositionalRules();
2585
2586 if (!childrenAffected && !descendantsAffected)
2587 return;
2588
2589 for (auto* sibling = elementAfterChange; sibling; sibling = sibling->nextElementSibling()) {
2590 if (childrenAffected)
2591 sibling->invalidateStyleInternal();
2592 if (descendantsAffected) {
2593 for (auto* siblingChild = sibling->firstElementChild(); siblingChild; siblingChild = siblingChild->nextElementSibling())
2594 siblingChild->invalidateStyleForSubtreeInternal();
2595 }
2596 }
2597}
2598
2599static void invalidateForBackwardPositionalRules(Element& parent, Element* elementBeforeChange)
2600{
2601 bool childrenAffected = parent.childrenAffectedByBackwardPositionalRules();
2602 bool descendantsAffected = parent.descendantsAffectedByBackwardPositionalRules();
2603
2604 if (!childrenAffected && !descendantsAffected)
2605 return;
2606
2607 for (auto* sibling = elementBeforeChange; sibling; sibling = sibling->previousElementSibling()) {
2608 if (childrenAffected)
2609 sibling->invalidateStyleInternal();
2610 if (descendantsAffected) {
2611 for (auto* siblingChild = sibling->firstElementChild(); siblingChild; siblingChild = siblingChild->nextElementSibling())
2612 siblingChild->invalidateStyleForSubtreeInternal();
2613 }
2614 }
2615}
2616
2617enum SiblingCheckType { FinishedParsingChildren, SiblingElementRemoved, Other };
2618
2619static void checkForSiblingStyleChanges(Element& parent, SiblingCheckType checkType, Element* elementBeforeChange, Element* elementAfterChange)
2620{
2621 // :empty selector.
2622 checkForEmptyStyleChange(parent);
2623
2624 if (parent.styleValidity() >= Style::Validity::SubtreeInvalid)
2625 return;
2626
2627 // :first-child. In the parser callback case, we don't have to check anything, since we were right the first time.
2628 // In the DOM case, we only need to do something if |afterChange| is not 0.
2629 // |afterChange| is 0 in the parser case, so it works out that we'll skip this block.
2630 if (parent.childrenAffectedByFirstChildRules() && elementAfterChange) {
2631 // Find our new first child.
2632 RefPtr<Element> newFirstElement = ElementTraversal::firstChild(parent);
2633 // Find the first element node following |afterChange|
2634
2635 // This is the insert/append case.
2636 if (newFirstElement != elementAfterChange) {
2637 auto* style = elementAfterChange->renderStyle();
2638 if (!style || style->firstChildState())
2639 elementAfterChange->invalidateStyleForSubtreeInternal();
2640 }
2641
2642 // We also have to handle node removal.
2643 if (checkType == SiblingElementRemoved && newFirstElement == elementAfterChange && newFirstElement) {
2644 auto* style = newFirstElement->renderStyle();
2645 if (!style || !style->firstChildState())
2646 newFirstElement->invalidateStyleForSubtreeInternal();
2647 }
2648 }
2649
2650 // :last-child. In the parser callback case, we don't have to check anything, since we were right the first time.
2651 // In the DOM case, we only need to do something if |afterChange| is not 0.
2652 if (parent.childrenAffectedByLastChildRules() && elementBeforeChange) {
2653 // Find our new last child.
2654 RefPtr<Element> newLastElement = ElementTraversal::lastChild(parent);
2655
2656 if (newLastElement != elementBeforeChange) {
2657 auto* style = elementBeforeChange->renderStyle();
2658 if (!style || style->lastChildState())
2659 elementBeforeChange->invalidateStyleForSubtreeInternal();
2660 }
2661
2662 // We also have to handle node removal. The parser callback case is similar to node removal as well in that we need to change the last child
2663 // to match now.
2664 if ((checkType == SiblingElementRemoved || checkType == FinishedParsingChildren) && newLastElement == elementBeforeChange && newLastElement) {
2665 auto* style = newLastElement->renderStyle();
2666 if (!style || !style->lastChildState())
2667 newLastElement->invalidateStyleForSubtreeInternal();
2668 }
2669 }
2670
2671 invalidateForSiblingCombinators(elementAfterChange);
2672
2673 invalidateForForwardPositionalRules(parent, elementAfterChange);
2674 invalidateForBackwardPositionalRules(parent, elementBeforeChange);
2675}
2676
2677void Element::childrenChanged(const ChildChange& change)
2678{
2679 ContainerNode::childrenChanged(change);
2680 if (change.source == ChildChange::Source::Parser)
2681 checkForEmptyStyleChange(*this);
2682 else {
2683 auto checkType = change.type == ChildChange::Type::ElementRemoved ? SiblingElementRemoved : Other;
2684 checkForSiblingStyleChanges(*this, checkType, change.previousSiblingElement, change.nextSiblingElement);
2685 }
2686
2687 if (ShadowRoot* shadowRoot = this->shadowRoot()) {
2688 switch (change.type) {
2689 case ChildChange::Type::ElementInserted:
2690 case ChildChange::Type::ElementRemoved:
2691 // For elements, we notify shadowRoot in Element::insertedIntoAncestor and Element::removedFromAncestor.
2692 break;
2693 case ChildChange::Type::AllChildrenRemoved:
2694 case ChildChange::Type::AllChildrenReplaced:
2695 shadowRoot->didRemoveAllChildrenOfShadowHost();
2696 break;
2697 case ChildChange::Type::TextInserted:
2698 case ChildChange::Type::TextRemoved:
2699 case ChildChange::Type::TextChanged:
2700 shadowRoot->didChangeDefaultSlot();
2701 break;
2702 case ChildChange::Type::NonContentsChildInserted:
2703 case ChildChange::Type::NonContentsChildRemoved:
2704 break;
2705 }
2706 }
2707}

2733static void appendAttributes(StringBuilder& builder, const Element& element)
2734{
2735 if (element.hasID())
2736 builder.append(" id=\'", element.getIdAttribute(), '\'');
2737
2738 if (element.hasClass()) {
2739 builder.append(" class=\'");
2740 size_t classNamesToDump = element.classNames().size();
2741 constexpr size_t maxNumClassNames = 7;
2742 bool addEllipsis = false;
2743 if (classNamesToDump > maxNumClassNames) {
2744 classNamesToDump = maxNumClassNames;
2745 addEllipsis = true;
2746 }
2747
2748 for (size_t i = 0; i < classNamesToDump; ++i) {
2749 if (i > 0)
2750 builder.append(' ');
2751 builder.append(element.classNames()[i]);
2752 }

2796
2797ExceptionOr<RefPtr<Attr>> Element::setAttributeNode(Attr& attrNode)
2798{
2799 RefPtr<Attr> oldAttrNode = attrIfExists(attrNode.localName(), shouldIgnoreAttributeCase(*this));
2800 if (oldAttrNode.get() == &attrNode)
2801 return oldAttrNode;
2802
2803 // InUseAttributeError: Raised if node is an Attr that is already an attribute of another Element object.
2804 // The DOM user must explicitly clone Attr nodes to re-use them in other elements.
2805 if (attrNode.ownerElement() && attrNode.ownerElement() != this)
2806 return Exception { InUseAttributeError };
2807
2808 {
2809 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
2810 synchronizeAllAttributes();
2811 }
2812
2813 auto& elementData = ensureUniqueElementData();
2814
2815 auto existingAttributeIndex = elementData.findAttributeIndexByName(attrNode.localName(), shouldIgnoreAttributeCase(*this));
2816
2817 // Attr::value() will return its 'm_standaloneValue' member any time its Element is set to nullptr. We need to cache this value
2818 // before making changes to attrNode's Element connections.
2819 auto attrNodeValue = attrNode.value();
2820
2821 if (existingAttributeIndex == ElementData::attributeNotFound) {
2822 attachAttributeNodeIfNeeded(attrNode);
2823 setAttributeInternal(elementData.findAttributeIndexByName(attrNode.qualifiedName()), attrNode.qualifiedName(), attrNodeValue, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
2824 } else {
2825 const Attribute& attribute = attributeAt(existingAttributeIndex);
2826 if (oldAttrNode)
2827 detachAttrNodeFromElementWithValue(oldAttrNode.get(), attribute.value());
2828 else
2829 oldAttrNode = Attr::create(document(), attrNode.qualifiedName(), attribute.value());
2830
2831 attachAttributeNodeIfNeeded(attrNode);
2832
2833 if (attribute.name().matches(attrNode.qualifiedName()))
2834 setAttributeInternal(existingAttributeIndex, attrNode.qualifiedName(), attrNodeValue, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
2835 else {
2836 removeAttributeInternal(existingAttributeIndex, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
2837 setAttributeInternal(ensureUniqueElementData().findAttributeIndexByName(attrNode.qualifiedName()), attrNode.qualifiedName(), attrNodeValue, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
2838 }
2839 }
2840
2841 return oldAttrNode;
2842}
2843
2844ExceptionOr<RefPtr<Attr>> Element::setAttributeNodeNS(Attr& attrNode)
2845{
2846 RefPtr<Attr> oldAttrNode = attrIfExists(attrNode.qualifiedName());
2847 if (oldAttrNode.get() == &attrNode)
2848 return oldAttrNode;
2849
2850 // InUseAttributeError: Raised if node is an Attr that is already an attribute of another Element object.
2851 // The DOM user must explicitly clone Attr nodes to re-use them in other elements.
2852 if (attrNode.ownerElement() && attrNode.ownerElement() != this)
2853 return Exception { InUseAttributeError };
2854
2855 // Attr::value() will return its 'm_standaloneValue' member any time its Element is set to nullptr. We need to cache this value
2856 // before making changes to attrNode's Element connections.
2857 auto attrNodeValue = attrNode.value();
2858 unsigned index = 0;
2859 {
2860 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
2861 synchronizeAllAttributes();
2862 auto& elementData = ensureUniqueElementData();
2863
2864 index = elementData.findAttributeIndexByName(attrNode.qualifiedName());
2865
2866 if (index != ElementData::attributeNotFound) {
2867 if (oldAttrNode)
2868 detachAttrNodeFromElementWithValue(oldAttrNode.get(), elementData.attributeAt(index).value());
2869 else
2870 oldAttrNode = Attr::create(document(), attrNode.qualifiedName(), elementData.attributeAt(index).value());
2871 }
2872 }
2873
2874 attachAttributeNodeIfNeeded(attrNode);
2875 setAttributeInternal(index, attrNode.qualifiedName(), attrNodeValue, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
2876
2877 return oldAttrNode;
2878}

2880ExceptionOr<Ref<Attr>> Element::removeAttributeNode(Attr& attr)
2881{
2882 if (attr.ownerElement() != this)
2883 return Exception { NotFoundError };
2884
2885 ASSERT(&document() == &attr.document());
2886
2887 synchronizeAllAttributes();
2888
2889 if (!m_elementData)
2890 return Exception { NotFoundError };
2891
2892 auto existingAttributeIndex = m_elementData->findAttributeIndexByName(attr.qualifiedName());
2893 if (existingAttributeIndex == ElementData::attributeNotFound)
2894 return Exception { NotFoundError };
2895
2896 Ref<Attr> oldAttrNode { attr };
2897
2898 detachAttrNodeFromElementWithValue(&attr, m_elementData->attributeAt(existingAttributeIndex).value());
2899 removeAttributeInternal(existingAttributeIndex, NotInSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute);
2900
2901 return oldAttrNode;
2902}

2924void Element::removeAttributeInternal(unsigned index, SynchronizationOfLazyAttribute inSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute)
2925{
2926 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(index < attributeCount());
2927
2928 UniqueElementData& elementData = ensureUniqueElementData();
2929
2930 QualifiedName name = elementData.attributeAt(index).name();
2931 AtomString valueBeingRemoved = elementData.attributeAt(index).value();
2932
2933 if (RefPtr<Attr> attrNode = attrIfExists(name))
2934 detachAttrNodeFromElementWithValue(attrNode.get(), elementData.attributeAt(index).value());
2935
2936 if (inSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute) {
2937 elementData.removeAttribute(index);
2938 return;
2939 }
2940
2941 ASSERT(!valueBeingRemoved.isNull());
2942 willModifyAttribute(name, valueBeingRemoved, nullAtom());
2943 {
2944 Style::AttributeChangeInvalidation styleInvalidation(*this, name, valueBeingRemoved, nullAtom());
2945 elementData.removeAttribute(index);
2946 }
2947
2948 didRemoveAttribute(name, valueBeingRemoved);
2949}
2950
2951void Element::addAttributeInternal(const QualifiedName& name, const AtomString& value, SynchronizationOfLazyAttribute inSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute)
2952{
2953 if (inSynchronizationOfLazyAttribute) {
2954 ensureUniqueElementData().addAttribute(name, value);
2955 return;
2956 }
2957
2958 willModifyAttribute(name, nullAtom(), value);
2959 {
2960 Style::AttributeChangeInvalidation styleInvalidation(*this, name, nullAtom(), value);
2961 ensureUniqueElementData().addAttribute(name, value);
2962 }
2963 didAddAttribute(name, value);
2964}

3037static bool isProgramaticallyFocusable(Element& element)
3038{
3039 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
3040
3041 if (shadowRootWithDelegatesFocus(element))
3042 return false;
3043
3044 // If the stylesheets have already been loaded we can reliably check isFocusable.
3045 // If not, we continue and set the focused node on the focus controller below so that it can be updated soon after attach.
3046 if (element.document().haveStylesheetsLoaded()) {
3047 if (!element.isFocusable())
3048 return false;
3049 }
3050 return element.supportsFocus();
3051}

3061 return &element;

3066void Element::focus(const FocusOptions& options)
3067{
3068 if (!isConnected())
3069 return;
3070
3071 auto document = makeRef(this->document());
3072 if (document->focusedElement() == this) {
3073 if (document->page())
3074 document->page()->chrome().client().elementDidRefocus(*this);
3075 return;
3076 }
3077
3078 RefPtr<Element> newTarget = this;
3079
3080 // If we don't have renderer yet, isFocusable will compute it without style update.
3081 // FIXME: Expand it to avoid style update in all cases.
3082 if (renderer() && document->haveStylesheetsLoaded())
3083 document->updateStyleIfNeeded();
3084
3085 if (&newTarget->document() != document.ptr())
3086 return;
3087
3088 if (auto root = shadowRootWithDelegatesFocus(*this)) {
3089 auto currentlyFocusedElement = makeRefPtr(document->focusedElement());
3090 if (root->containsIncludingShadowDOM(currentlyFocusedElement.get())) {
3091 if (document->page())
3092 document->page()->chrome().client().elementDidRefocus(*currentlyFocusedElement);
3093 return;
3094 }
3095
3096 newTarget = findFirstProgramaticallyFocusableElementInComposedTree(*this);
3097 if (!newTarget)
3098 return;
3099 } else if (!isProgramaticallyFocusable(*newTarget))
3100 return;
3101
3102 if (Page* page = document->page()) {
3103 auto& frame = *document->frame();
3104 if (!frame.hasHadUserInteraction() && !frame.isMainFrame() && !document->topDocument().securityOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(document->securityOrigin()))
3105 return;
3106
3107 FocusOptions optionsWithVisibility = options;
3108 if (!document->wasLastFocusByClick())
3109 optionsWithVisibility.visibility = FocusVisibility::Visible;
3110
3111 // Focus and change event handlers can cause us to lose our last ref.
3112 // If a focus event handler changes the focus to a different node it
3113 // does not make sense to continue and update appearence.
3114 if (!page->focusController().setFocusedElement(newTarget.get(), *document->frame(), optionsWithVisibility))
3115 return;
3116 }
3117
3118 newTarget->findTargetAndUpdateFocusAppearance(options.selectionRestorationMode, options.preventScroll ? SelectionRevealMode::DoNotReveal : SelectionRevealMode::Reveal);
3119}
3120
3121void Element::findTargetAndUpdateFocusAppearance(SelectionRestorationMode selectionMode, SelectionRevealMode revealMode)
3122{
3123#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3124 // Focusing a form element triggers animation in UIKit to scroll to the right position.
3125 // Calling updateFocusAppearance() would generate an unnecessary call to ScrollView::setScrollPosition(),
3126 // which would jump us around during this animation. See <rdar://problem/6699741>.
3127 if (revealMode == SelectionRevealMode::Reveal && is<HTMLFormControlElement>(*this))
3128 revealMode = SelectionRevealMode::RevealUpToMainFrame;
3129#endif
3130
3131 auto target = focusAppearanceUpdateTarget();
3132 if (!target)
3133 return;
3134
3135 target->updateFocusAppearance(selectionMode, revealMode);
3136}

3140{
3141 return this;

3143
3144void Element::updateFocusAppearance(SelectionRestorationMode, SelectionRevealMode revealMode)
3145{
3146 if (isRootEditableElement()) {
3147 // Keep frame alive in this method, since setSelection() may release the last reference to |frame|.
3148 RefPtr<Frame> frame = document().frame();
3149 if (!frame)
3150 return;
3151
3152 // When focusing an editable element in an iframe, don't reset the selection if it already contains a selection.
3153 if (this == frame->selection().selection().rootEditableElement())
3154 return;
3155
3156 // FIXME: We should restore the previous selection if there is one.
3157 VisibleSelection newSelection = VisibleSelection(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(this));
3158
3159 if (frame->selection().shouldChangeSelection(newSelection)) {
3160 frame->selection().setSelection(newSelection, FrameSelection::defaultSetSelectionOptions(), Element::defaultFocusTextStateChangeIntent());
3161 frame->selection().revealSelection(revealMode);
3162 return;
3163 }
3164 }
3165
3166 if (RefPtr<FrameView> view = document().view())
3167 view->scheduleScrollToFocusedElement(revealMode);
3168}

3256ExceptionOr<void> Element::setOuterHTML(const String& html)
3257{
3258 // The specification allows setting outerHTML on an Element whose parent is a DocumentFragment and Gecko supports this.
3259 // However, as of June 2021, Blink matches our behavior and throws a NoModificationAllowedError for non-Element parents.
3260 RefPtr parent = parentElement();
3261 if (UNLIKELY(!parent)) {
3262 if (!parentNode())
3263 return Exception { NoModificationAllowedError, "Cannot set outerHTML on element because it doesn't have a parent" };
3264 return Exception { NoModificationAllowedError, "Cannot set outerHTML on element because its parent is not an Element" };
3265 }
3266
3267 RefPtr<Node> prev = previousSibling();
3268 RefPtr<Node> next = nextSibling();
3269
3270 auto fragment = createFragmentForInnerOuterHTML(*parent, html, AllowScriptingContent);
3271 if (fragment.hasException())
3272 return fragment.releaseException();
3273
3274 auto replaceResult = parent->replaceChild(fragment.releaseReturnValue().get(), *this);
3275 if (replaceResult.hasException())
3276 return replaceResult.releaseException();
3277
3278 // The following is not part of the specification but matches Blink's behavior as of June 2021.
3279 RefPtr<Node> node = next ? next->previousSibling() : nullptr;
3280 if (is<Text>(node)) {
3281 auto result = mergeWithNextTextNode(downcast<Text>(*node));
3282 if (result.hasException())
3283 return result.releaseException();
3284 }
3285 if (is<Text>(prev)) {
3286 auto result = mergeWithNextTextNode(downcast<Text>(*prev));
3287 if (result.hasException())
3288 return result.releaseException();
3289 }
3290 return { };
3291}
3292
3293ExceptionOr<void> Element::setInnerHTML(const String& html)
3294{
3295 auto fragment = createFragmentForInnerOuterHTML(*this, html, AllowScriptingContent);
3296 if (fragment.hasException())
3297 return fragment.releaseException();
3298
3299 ContainerNode* container;
3300 if (!is<HTMLTemplateElement>(*this))
3301 container = this;
3302 else
3303 container = &downcast<HTMLTemplateElement>(*this).content();
3304
3305 return replaceChildrenWithFragment(*container, fragment.releaseReturnValue());
3306}
