3410const RenderStyle* Element::resolveComputedStyle(ResolveComputedStyleMode mode)
3411{
3412 ASSERT(isConnected());
3413 ASSERT(!existingComputedStyle() || hasNodeFlag(NodeFlag::IsComputedStyleInvalidFlag));
3414
3415 Deque<RefPtr<Element>, 32> elementsRequiringComputedStyle({ this });
3416 const RenderStyle* computedStyle = nullptr;
3417
3418 // Collect ancestors until we find one that has style.
3419 for (auto& ancestor : composedTreeAncestors(*this)) {
3420 if (auto* existingStyle = ancestor.existingComputedStyle()) {
3421 computedStyle = existingStyle;
3422 break;
3423 }
3424 elementsRequiringComputedStyle.prepend(&ancestor);
3425 }
3426
3427 // On iOS request delegates called during styleForElement may result in re-entering WebKit and killing the style resolver.
3428 Style::PostResolutionCallbackDisabler disabler(document(), Style::PostResolutionCallbackDisabler::DrainCallbacks::No);
3429
3430 // Resolve and cache styles starting from the most distant ancestor.
3431 for (auto& element : elementsRequiringComputedStyle) {
3432 auto style = document().styleForElementIgnoringPendingStylesheets(*element, computedStyle);
3433 computedStyle = style.get();
3434 ElementRareData& rareData = element->ensureElementRareData();
3435 rareData.setComputedStyle(WTFMove(style));
3436 element->clearNodeFlag(NodeFlag::IsComputedStyleInvalidFlag);
3437
3438 if (mode == ResolveComputedStyleMode::RenderedOnly && computedStyle->display() == DisplayType::None)
3439 return nullptr;
3440 }
3441
3442 return computedStyle;
3443}
3444
3445bool Element::hasValidStyle() const
3446{
3447 if (!document().needsStyleRecalc())
3448 return true;
3449
3450 if (document().hasPendingFullStyleRebuild())
3451 return false;
3452
3453 for (auto& element : lineageOfType<Element>(*this)) {
3454 if (element.styleValidity() != Style::Validity::Valid)
3455 return false;
3456 }
3457 return true;
3458}
3459
3460bool Element::isVisibleWithoutResolvingFullStyle() const
3461{
3462 document().styleScope().flushPendingUpdate();
3463
3464 if (renderStyle() || hasValidStyle())
3465 return renderStyle() && renderStyle()->visibility() == Visibility::Visible;
3466
3467 auto computedStyleForElement = [](Element& element) -> const RenderStyle* {
3468 auto* style = element.hasNodeFlag(NodeFlag::IsComputedStyleInvalidFlag) ? nullptr : element.existingComputedStyle();
3469 return style ? style : element.resolveComputedStyle(ResolveComputedStyleMode::RenderedOnly);
3470 };
3471
3472 // Compute style in yet unstyled subtree.
3473 auto* style = computedStyleForElement(const_cast<Element&>(*this));
3474 if (!style)
3475 return false;
3476
3477 if (style->display() == DisplayType::None || style->display() == DisplayType::Contents)
3478 return false;
3479
3480 if (style->visibility() != Visibility::Visible)
3481 return false;
3482
3483 for (auto& element : composedTreeAncestors(const_cast<Element&>(*this))) {
3484 auto* style = computedStyleForElement(element);
3485 if (!style || style->display() == DisplayType::None)
3486 return false;
3487 }
3488
3489 return true;
3490}
3491
3492const RenderStyle& Element::resolvePseudoElementStyle(PseudoId pseudoElementSpecifier)
3493{
3494 ASSERT(!isPseudoElement());
3495
3496 auto* parentStyle = existingComputedStyle();
3497 ASSERT(parentStyle);
3498 ASSERT(!parentStyle->getCachedPseudoStyle(pseudoElementSpecifier));
3499
3500 Style::PostResolutionCallbackDisabler disabler(document(), Style::PostResolutionCallbackDisabler::DrainCallbacks::No);
3501
3502 auto style = document().styleForElementIgnoringPendingStylesheets(*this, parentStyle, pseudoElementSpecifier);
3503 if (!style) {
3504 style = RenderStyle::createPtr();
3505 style->inheritFrom(*parentStyle);
3506 style->setStyleType(pseudoElementSpecifier);
3507 }
3508
3509 auto* computedStyle = style.get();
3510 const_cast<RenderStyle*>(parentStyle)->addCachedPseudoStyle(WTFMove(style));
3511 return *computedStyle;
3512}
3513
3514const RenderStyle* Element::computedStyle(PseudoId pseudoElementSpecifier)
3515{
3516 if (!isConnected())
3517 return nullptr;
3518
3519 if (PseudoElement* pseudoElement = beforeOrAfterPseudoElement(*this, pseudoElementSpecifier))
3520 return pseudoElement->computedStyle();
3521
3522 auto* style = existingComputedStyle();
3523 if (!style)
3524 style = resolveComputedStyle();
3525
3526 if (pseudoElementSpecifier != PseudoId::None) {
3527 if (auto* cachedPseudoStyle = style->getCachedPseudoStyle(pseudoElementSpecifier))
3528 return cachedPseudoStyle;
3529 return &resolvePseudoElementStyle(pseudoElementSpecifier);
3530 }
3531
3532 return style;
3533}

4059

4067void Element::updateNameForTreeScope(TreeScope& scope, const AtomString& oldName, const AtomString& newName)
4068{
4069 ASSERT(oldName != newName);
4070
4071 if (!oldName.isEmpty())
4072 scope.removeElementByName(*oldName.impl(), *this);
4073 if (!newName.isEmpty())
4074 scope.addElementByName(*newName.impl(), *this);

4076
4077void Element::updateNameForDocument(HTMLDocument& document, const AtomString& oldName, const AtomString& newName)
4078{
4079 ASSERT(oldName != newName);
4080
4081 if (isInShadowTree())
4082 return;
4083
4084 if (WindowNameCollection::elementMatchesIfNameAttributeMatch(*this)) {
4085 const AtomString& id = WindowNameCollection::elementMatchesIfIdAttributeMatch(*this) ? getIdAttribute() : nullAtom();
4086 if (!oldName.isEmpty() && oldName != id)
4087 document.removeWindowNamedItem(*oldName.impl(), *this);
4088 if (!newName.isEmpty() && newName != id)
4089 document.addWindowNamedItem(*newName.impl(), *this);
4090 }
4091
4092 if (DocumentNameCollection::elementMatchesIfNameAttributeMatch(*this)) {
4093 const AtomString& id = DocumentNameCollection::elementMatchesIfIdAttributeMatch(*this) ? getIdAttribute() : nullAtom();
4094 if (!oldName.isEmpty() && oldName != id)
4095 document.removeDocumentNamedItem(*oldName.impl(), *this);
4096 if (!newName.isEmpty() && newName != id)
4097 document.addDocumentNamedItem(*newName.impl(), *this);
4098 }
4099}

4121 ASSERT(oldId != newId);
4122
4123 if (!oldId.isEmpty())
4124 scope.removeElementById(*oldId.impl(), *this, notifyObservers == NotifyObservers::Yes);
4125 if (!newId.isEmpty())
4126 scope.addElementById(*newId.impl(), *this, notifyObservers == NotifyObservers::Yes);

4128
4129void Element::updateIdForDocument(HTMLDocument& document, const AtomString& oldId, const AtomString& newId, HTMLDocumentNamedItemMapsUpdatingCondition condition)
4130{
4131 ASSERT(isConnected());
4132 ASSERT(oldId != newId);
4133
4134 if (isInShadowTree())
4135 return;
4136
4137 if (WindowNameCollection::elementMatchesIfIdAttributeMatch(*this)) {
4138 const AtomString& name = condition == UpdateHTMLDocumentNamedItemMapsOnlyIfDiffersFromNameAttribute && WindowNameCollection::elementMatchesIfNameAttributeMatch(*this) ? getNameAttribute() : nullAtom();
4139 if (!oldId.isEmpty() && oldId != name)
4140 document.removeWindowNamedItem(*oldId.impl(), *this);
4141 if (!newId.isEmpty() && newId != name)
4142 document.addWindowNamedItem(*newId.impl(), *this);
4143 }
4144
4145 if (DocumentNameCollection::elementMatchesIfIdAttributeMatch(*this)) {
4146 const AtomString& name = condition == UpdateHTMLDocumentNamedItemMapsOnlyIfDiffersFromNameAttribute && DocumentNameCollection::elementMatchesIfNameAttributeMatch(*this) ? getNameAttribute() : nullAtom();
4147 if (!oldId.isEmpty() && oldId != name)

4372void Element::cloneAttributesFromElement(const Element& other)
4373{
4374 if (hasSyntheticAttrChildNodes())
4375 detachAllAttrNodesFromElement();
4376
4377 other.synchronizeAllAttributes();
4378 if (!other.m_elementData) {
4379 m_elementData = nullptr;
4380 return;
4381 }
4382
4383 // We can't update window and document's named item maps since the presence of image and object elements depend on other attributes and children.
4384 // Fortunately, those named item maps are only updated when this element is in the document, which should never be the case.
4385 ASSERT(!isConnected());
4386
4387 const AtomString& oldID = getIdAttribute();
4388 const AtomString& newID = other.getIdAttribute();
4389
4390 if (!oldID.isNull() || !newID.isNull())
4391 updateId(oldID, newID, NotifyObservers::No); // Will notify observers after the attribute is actually changed.
4392
4393 const AtomString& oldName = getNameAttribute();
4394 const AtomString& newName = other.getNameAttribute();
4395
4396 if (!oldName.isNull() || !newName.isNull())
4397 updateName(oldName, newName);
4398
4399 // If 'other' has a mutable ElementData, convert it to an immutable one so we can share it between both elements.
4400 // We can only do this if there is no CSSOM wrapper for other's inline style, and there are no presentation attributes.
4401 if (is<UniqueElementData>(*other.m_elementData)
4402 && !other.m_elementData->presentationalHintStyle()
4403 && (!other.m_elementData->inlineStyle() || !other.m_elementData->inlineStyle()->hasCSSOMWrapper()))
4404 const_cast<Element&>(other).m_elementData = downcast<UniqueElementData>(*other.m_elementData).makeShareableCopy();
4405
4406 if (!other.m_elementData->isUnique())
4407 m_elementData = other.m_elementData;
4408 else
4409 m_elementData = other.m_elementData->makeUniqueCopy();
4410
4411 for (const Attribute& attribute : attributesIterator())
4412 attributeChanged(attribute.name(), nullAtom(), attribute.value(), ModifiedByCloning);
4413}

4439ExceptionOr<Node*> Element::insertAdjacent(const String& where, Ref<Node>&& newChild)
4440{
4441 // In Internet Explorer if the element has no parent and where is "beforeBegin" or "afterEnd",
4442 // a document fragment is created and the elements appended in the correct order. This document
4443 // fragment isn't returned anywhere.
4444 //
4445 // This is impossible for us to implement as the DOM tree does not allow for such structures,
4446 // Opera also appears to disallow such usage.
4447
4448 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(where, "beforebegin")) {
4449 auto* parent = this->parentNode();
4450 if (!parent)
4451 return nullptr;
4452 auto result = parent->insertBefore(newChild, this);
4453 if (result.hasException())
4454 return result.releaseException();
4455 return newChild.ptr();
4456 }
4457
4458 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(where, "afterbegin")) {
4459 auto result = insertBefore(newChild, firstChild());
4460 if (result.hasException())
4461 return result.releaseException();
4462 return newChild.ptr();
4463 }
4464
4465 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(where, "beforeend")) {
4466 auto result = appendChild(newChild);
4467 if (result.hasException())
4468 return result.releaseException();
4469 return newChild.ptr();
4470 }
4471
4472 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(where, "afterend")) {
4473 auto* parent = this->parentNode();
4474 if (!parent)
4475 return nullptr;
4476 auto result = parent->insertBefore(newChild, nextSibling());
4477 if (result.hasException())
4478 return result.releaseException();
4479 return newChild.ptr();
4480 }
4481
4482 return Exception { SyntaxError };
4483}

4493// Step 1 of https://w3c.github.io/DOM-Parsing/#dom-element-insertadjacenthtml.
4494static ExceptionOr<ContainerNode&> contextNodeForInsertion(const String& where, Element& element)
4495{
4496 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(where, "beforebegin") || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(where, "afterend")) {
4497 auto* parent = element.parentNode();
4498 if (!parent || is<Document>(*parent))
4499 return Exception { NoModificationAllowedError };
4500 return *parent;
4501 }
4502 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(where, "afterbegin") || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(where, "beforeend"))
4503 return element;
4504 return Exception { SyntaxError };
4505}
4506
4507// Step 2 of https://w3c.github.io/DOM-Parsing/#dom-element-insertadjacenthtml.
4508static ExceptionOr<Ref<Element>> contextElementForInsertion(const String& where, Element& element)
4509{
4510 auto contextNodeResult = contextNodeForInsertion(where, element);
4511 if (contextNodeResult.hasException())
4512 return contextNodeResult.releaseException();
4513 auto& contextNode = contextNodeResult.releaseReturnValue();
4514 if (!is<Element>(contextNode) || (contextNode.document().isHTMLDocument() && is<HTMLHtmlElement>(contextNode)))
4515 return Ref<Element> { HTMLBodyElement::create(contextNode.document()) };
4516 return Ref<Element> { downcast<Element>(contextNode) };
4517}

4519// https://w3c.github.io/DOM-Parsing/#dom-element-insertadjacenthtml
4520ExceptionOr<void> Element::insertAdjacentHTML(const String& where, const String& markup, NodeVector* addedNodes)
4521{
4522 // Steps 1 and 2.
4523 auto contextElement = contextElementForInsertion(where, *this);
4524 if (contextElement.hasException())
4525 return contextElement.releaseException();
4526 // Step 3.
4527 auto fragment = createFragmentForInnerOuterHTML(contextElement.releaseReturnValue(), markup, AllowScriptingContent);
4528 if (fragment.hasException())
4529 return fragment.releaseException();
4530
4531 if (UNLIKELY(addedNodes)) {
4532 // Must be called before insertAdjacent, as otherwise the children of fragment will be moved
4533 // to their new parent and will be harder to keep track of.
4534 *addedNodes = collectChildNodes(fragment.returnValue());
4535 }
4536
4537 // Step 4.
4538 auto result = insertAdjacent(where, fragment.releaseReturnValue());
4539 if (result.hasException())
4540 return result.releaseException();
4541 return { };
4542}

4557Element* Element::findAnchorElementForLink(String& outAnchorName)
4558{

4560 return nullptr;

4562 const AtomString& href = attributeWithoutSynchronization(HTMLNames::hrefAttr);
4563 if (href.isNull())

4572 outAnchorName = url.fragmentIdentifier().toString();

4576 return nullptr;

4579ExceptionOr<Ref<WebAnimation>> Element::animate(JSC::JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, JSC::Strong<JSC::JSObject>&& keyframes, std::optional<Variant<double, KeyframeAnimationOptions>>&& options)
4580{

4583 if (options) {

4586 if (WTF::holds_alternative<double>(optionsValue))
4587 keyframeEffectOptionsVariant = WTF::get<double>(optionsValue);
4588 else {
4589 auto keyframeEffectOptions = WTF::get<KeyframeAnimationOptions>(optionsValue);

4591 keyframeEffectOptionsVariant = WTFMove(keyframeEffectOptions);

4597 if (keyframeEffectResult.hasException())

4604 if (animationPlayResult.hasException())
4605 return animationPlayResult.releaseException();

4610Vector<RefPtr<WebAnimation>> Element::getAnimations(std::optional<GetAnimationsOptions> options)
4611{
4612 // If we are to return animations in the subtree, we can get all of the document's animations and filter
4613 // animations targeting that are not registered on this element, one of its pseudo elements or a child's
4614 // pseudo element.
4615 if (options && options->subtree) {
4616 return document().matchingAnimations([&] (Element& target) -> bool {
4617 if (is<PseudoElement>(target))
4618 return contains(downcast<PseudoElement>(target).hostElement());
4619 return contains(&target);
4620 });
4621 }
4622
4623 // For the list of animations to be current, we need to account for any pending CSS changes,
4624 // such as updates to CSS Animations and CSS Transitions.
4625 // FIXME: We might be able to use ComputedStyleExtractor which is more optimized.
4626 document().updateStyleIfNeeded();
4627
4628 Vector<RefPtr<WebAnimation>> animations;
4629 if (auto* effectStack = keyframeEffectStack(PseudoId::None)) {
4630 for (auto& effect : effectStack->sortedEffects()) {
4631 if (effect->animation()->isRelevant())
4632 animations.append(effect->animation());
4633 }
4634 }
4635 return animations;
4636}
